<p>Tom began playing the guitar when he was 13 years old. His very first guitar was a $25 acoustic that his parents purchased from the Sears & Roebuck. Fast forward to today, Tom plays custom built <b>Stratocasters</b> built by the Haywire Custom Guitar shop. For amplification, he uses <b>The Peavey Classic 30</b>. His assortment of effects is made by BOSS & Morely. The <b>Boss Metal Core distortion</b>, <b>Digital Delay DD 7</b> & <b>BOSS Graphic GE - 7 EQ</b>, are of his main effects. The Original Morley <b> Bad Horsie Wah pedal</b> endorsed by Steve Vai, completes his effect line up. The microphones of Tom`s choice are of various brands. Heil, Stagg, AKG & Shure are included in his collection.<br />
<br />
His style of guitar playing is that of Blues / Rock which can be heard in his playing. Tom`s main influence of guitar playing came from the Legendary, Stevie Ray Vaughan. In his vocal arrangements he is influenced by several artists such as Elvis Presley & Neil Diamond. The nature is definetly that of the blues nature. So, please take a listen. You will be sure to enjoy his music.</p>
